Here's a possible implementation of the `q_and_a_extractor` function in Julia:

```julia
function q_and_a_extractor(md)
    question = match(r"# Question\n(.+?)# Answer", md, s"""m""") do m
        return strip(m.captures[1])
    end

    answer = match(r"# Answer\n(.+)", md, s"""m""") do m
        return strip(m.captures[1])
    end

    return (question, answer)
end
```

This function uses regular expressions to match the question and answer sections in the markdown text `md`, and then strips any leading spaces and newlines from the extracted text. You can use this function to extract the question and answer from the given markdown-formatted text.
